## 8. Reflection

Enterprise systems need event-driven behavior because actions must happen automatically whenever data changes.

Examples:
- Notifications
- Record updates
- Alerts
- Approval processes

Without automation, employees would need to do everything manually, which increases:
- Errors
- Delays
- Workload

Triggers and Flows help systems react intelligently to business events in real time.

